* TL331 - behavioral model with VCC detection
* Pins: 1=IN- 2=GND 3=IN+ 4=OUT 5=VCC
*
.SUBCKT TL331 IN- GND IN+ OUT VCC
* IN+ > IN- -> OUT Hi-Z (HIGH via pullup resistor)
* IN+ < IN- -> OUT LOW (sinking to GND)

* Gain stage: AV=100 keeps internal voltages <2kV for convergence
E331_MID MID_IN GND VALUE = { 100 * (V(IN-) - V(IN+)) }

* Open-drain output switch: ON when MID_IN > 2V (20mV input-referred)
S331_OUT MID_OUT GND MID_IN 0 TL331_SW
.MODEL TL331_SW SW(VT=1.0 VH=2.0 RON=10 ROFF=1e12)

* VCC detection: VCC < 5V -> output disconnected (comparator dead)
S_VCC OUT MID_OUT VCC 0 VCCSW
.MODEL VCCSW SW(VT=5 VH=1 RON=10 ROFF=1e12)

* Parasitic capacitances
C331_INP IN+ GND 1p
C331_INN IN- GND 1p
C331_OUT OUT GND 2p

.ENDS TL331
